Emacs TLDR

C means Control.
M means Alt/Option/Esc.
RET means Enter.
SPC means Space.

Most Used

  C-g        cancel current command or prompt
  C-x C-f    open/create file
  C-x C-s    save file
  C-x C-c    quit Emacs

Windows

These are Emacs windows, not macOS windows.

  C-x o      switch to the other window
  C-x 0      close current window
  C-x 1      keep only current window
  C-x 2      split window top/bottom
  C-x 3      split window left/right

Buffers

Buffers are open files or internal Emacs pages.

  C-x b      switch buffer
  C-x C-b    list buffers
  C-x k      close/kill current buffer

Select, Copy, Paste

Start selection:

  C-SPC
  C-c SPC    fallback if macOS steals C-SPC

Move cursor to select text. The selected region should be highlighted.

  C-w        cut selected text
  M-w        copy selected text
  C-y        paste
  M-y        cycle older clipboard entries after paste

Undo and Redo

With the setup in ~/.emacs.d/init.el:

  C-z        undo
  C-S-z      redo

Movement

  C-n        next line
  C-p        previous line
  C-f        forward char
  C-b        back char

  M-f        forward word
  M-b        back word

  C-a        start of line
  C-e        end of line
  M-<        start of file
  M->        end of file

Delete

  DEL        delete previous char
  C-d        delete next char
  M-d        delete next word
  C-k        cut from cursor to end of line

Search

  C-s        search

Type search text. Press C-s again for next match. Press RET to stop.

Compile

With the setup in ~/.emacs.d/init.el:

  C-c c      set compile command
  F5         rerun compile

Example compile command:

  cc main.c -o main && ./main

Best Habit

When stuck, press:

  C-g

It cancels whatever mode/prompt you are in.
